I am getting the following error message when trying to connect to a hub:
`Error: Failed to start the connection: Error: Unable to initialize any of the available transports.`

I am using the following packages:

Server is a .net core API:
-     Microsoft.AspNetCore.All - Version="2.0.5"  
-     Microsoft.AspNetCore.SignalR - Version="1.0.0-preview1-final" 

Client is an Angular 6 cli app:
- @aspnet/signalr - version "^1.0.0-rc1-update1"

I am currently developing my application with VS 2017 & VS Code using IIS Express on Windows 10 (both client & server). The issue occurs on all browsers, though I am mainly using the latest stable Chrome. 

Here is the client:
```
import { NGXLogger } from 'ngx-logger';
import { Component, OnInit, OnDestroy } from '@angular/core';
import { HubConnection } from '@aspnet/signalr';
import { Router } from '@angular/router';
import * as signalR from '@aspnet/signalr';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-operation-list',
  templateUrl: './operation-list.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./operation-list.component.scss']
})
export class OperationListComponent implements OnInit, OnDestroy {

  private hub: HubConnection;
  private data: Operation[];

  constructor(private progressBarService: ProgressBarService,
    private logger: NGXLogger,
    private authService: AuthenticationService,
    private router: Router) {

    this.data = [];
    this.progressBarService.show();

    const user = this.authService.getCurrentUser();

    this.hub = new signalR.HubConnectionBuilder()
      .configureLogging(signalR.LogLevel.Trace)
      .withUrl(`${environment.apiUrl}emergency-operations?token=${user.token}`)
      .build();

    this.hub.on('GetOperations', (data: Operation[]) => {
      this.logger.trace(`Retrieved ${data.length} operations`);
      this.data = data;
      this.progressBarService.hide();
    });

  }

  ngOnInit() {
    this.hub.start()
      .then(() => {
        this.logger.trace('Hub started');
        this.progressBarService.show();
        this.hub.invoke('GetOperations');
      })
      .catch((e) => {
        this.logger.error(`An error occurred while connecting to operations hub. Details ${e}`);
        this.notificationService.openSnackBar('Error while establishing connection');
        this.progressBarService.hide();
      });

  }

  ngOnDestroy() {
    this.hub.stop()
      .then(() => {
        this.logger.trace('Hub stopped.');
      });
  }

```

