I believe the problem is that I am not specifying the transport type. Notice the log above:

`Debug: Skipping transport 'undefined' because it is not supported by this client.`

I recently updated the client to the latest version from npm and the library seems to have changed, it appears that the `HubConnectionBuilder` is used instead of the `HubConnection` class, whose constructor is now private. 

I was previously able to do the following to specify the transport type:

```
const options = {
      transport: TransportType.WebSockets
    };

    this.hub = new HubConnection(`${environment.apiUrl}emergency-operations?token=${user.token}`, options);
```

Since the `HubConnection` class constructor is now private and I have to use the builder to create the connection, how do I specify the transport type?

